00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:01:56,265 --> 00:01:57,345
One year,

2
00:01:58,065 --> 00:01:59,985
I had the hallway renovated.

3
00:02:01,185 --> 00:02:02,745
I hired a relative to take the job.

4
00:02:04,185 --> 00:02:08,105
Turns out there were quality issues.

5
00:02:08,185 --> 00:02:11,945
One resident slipped
on the stairs at night and died.

6
00:02:13,225 --> 00:02:14,185
I figured

7
00:02:14,265 --> 00:02:17,385
I should fix it before it got worse,
so I redid the hallway.

8
00:02:17,985 --> 00:02:19,105
But I had no money left.

9
00:02:20,145 --> 00:02:21,265
So I secretly

10
00:02:22,065 --> 00:02:25,545
took materials from maintenance
and got some supplies.

11
00:02:25,625 --> 00:02:27,025
I set up a small shack

12
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:28,705
in the parking garage
and stashed the materials there.

13
00:02:32,545 --> 00:02:33,385
Officer Ran,

14
00:02:35,145 --> 00:02:37,545
why did you go to the garage?

15
00:02:38,945 --> 00:02:41,025
I just thought, once I had enough,

16
00:02:41,105 --> 00:02:43,105
I'd fix it properly.

17
00:02:43,185 --> 00:02:46,225
You tell me, why'd he get so much cement?

18
00:02:47,665 --> 00:02:49,745
This cement must be about 100 kilos.

19
00:02:51,185 --> 00:02:52,225
But then,

20
00:02:54,745 --> 00:02:55,585
that year,

21
00:02:55,665 --> 00:02:58,065
Ju… July…

22
00:03:13,505 --> 00:03:15,545
Rats. I love catching rats.

23
00:03:15,625 --> 00:03:17,585
Xiaohe, slow down.

24
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:19,505
Xiaohe.

25
00:03:20,025 --> 00:03:23,785
Uncle Ran, this underground maze
is so cool!

26
00:03:23,865 --> 00:03:24,905
Xiaohe,

27
00:03:26,745 --> 00:03:28,425
stay close to me.

28
00:03:28,505 --> 00:03:30,105
What if a rat suddenly jumps out?

29
00:03:50,745 --> 00:03:52,545
<i>How would I know</i>

30
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:57,385
<i>there was a head and two arms</i>
<i>in that tool bag?</i>

31
00:03:59,825 --> 00:04:02,025
I did think about calling the police.

32
00:04:02,105 --> 00:04:03,065
Did you?

33
00:04:27,345 --> 00:04:29,305
-Who is it?
-<i>Qian Dajun.</i>

34
00:04:29,385 --> 00:04:30,905
<i>You brat!</i>

35
00:04:32,225 --> 00:04:33,545
Dad.

36
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:35,105
<i>Who are you calling Dad?</i>

37
00:04:35,185 --> 00:04:37,585
<i>When are you going to sell</i>
<i>the place in Yuanlongli?</i>

38
00:04:38,105 --> 00:04:39,105
Soon.

39
00:04:39,745 --> 00:04:41,505
-Soon.
-<i>Not a chance.</i>

40
00:04:41,585 --> 00:04:42,945
<i>I've heard about it!</i>

41
00:04:43,025 --> 00:04:44,465
<i>They say that place eats people.</i>

42
00:04:44,545 --> 00:04:46,585
<i>No one dares live there.</i>
<i>Prices are dropping like crazy.</i>

43
00:04:46,665 --> 00:04:47,625
<i>Back then,</i>

44
00:04:47,705 --> 00:04:50,345
<i>rumors were going around</i>
<i>that the place was killing people.</i>

45
00:04:50,865 --> 00:04:52,505
<i>If I'd called the police,</i>

46
00:04:52,585 --> 00:04:56,825
<i>neither my place nor my relatives'</i>
<i>would've sold.</i>

47
00:04:57,345 --> 00:04:59,305
<i>After thinking it through,</i>

48
00:04:59,385 --> 00:05:02,545
<i>I decided to keep it quiet.</i>

49
00:05:05,225 --> 00:05:08,465
I figured I'd find a safer place,

50
00:05:08,545 --> 00:05:10,665
hide it first,

51
00:05:10,745 --> 00:05:13,265
then deal with it when I got the chance.

52
00:05:15,865 --> 00:05:16,985
Careful, Xiaohe.

53
00:05:22,225 --> 00:05:24,225
<i>I put it in the chicken coop.</i>

54
00:05:25,425 --> 00:05:27,345
<i>I was afraid my uncle would find it.</i>

55
00:05:27,425 --> 00:05:28,665
<i>So I thought</i>

56
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,505
<i>I should move it to a safer place.</i>

57
00:05:32,945 --> 00:05:35,865
<i>But that drain inlet was too small.</i>

58
00:05:37,665 --> 00:05:39,705
<i>No matter what, it wouldn't fit.</i>

59
00:05:39,785 --> 00:05:42,785
<i>So I had to move it again.</i>

60
00:05:51,665 --> 00:05:54,865
When I came back,
I found the head was gone.

61
00:05:54,945 --> 00:05:56,705
I couldn't find it anywhere.

62
00:05:57,625 --> 00:05:59,025
So I took the bag

63
00:05:59,105 --> 00:06:01,465
and buried it
in the woods behind the complex.

64
00:06:01,985 --> 00:06:05,585
I was terrified for a long time,

65
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:08,025
having nightmares every day.

66
00:06:09,145 --> 00:06:11,905
I went on like that for five years.

67
00:06:12,585 --> 00:06:14,505
I thought it was over,

68
00:06:14,585 --> 00:06:15,945
but then,

69
00:06:17,865 --> 00:06:19,225
in the summer of 2002,

70
00:06:19,305 --> 00:06:23,065
my uncle, Ge Jingsong,
pulled the head out.

71
00:06:23,145 --> 00:06:25,305
Murder!

72
00:06:44,185 --> 00:06:45,705
<i>Officer Ran went like a man possessed,</i>

73
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:49,825
<i>tearing through the whole complex,</i>
<i>searching everywhere.</i>

74
00:06:49,905 --> 00:06:50,745
DANGER, ELECTRICITY

75
00:06:55,905 --> 00:06:58,025
I was guilty and scared,

76
00:06:58,665 --> 00:07:00,825
so I dug the bag back up

77
00:07:01,465 --> 00:07:02,305
and moved it.

78
00:07:02,385 --> 00:07:04,225
SO I MOVED THE BAG

79
00:07:04,305 --> 00:07:07,465
But later, I almost got caught
by Officer Ran.

80
00:07:15,225 --> 00:07:16,345
Open it.

81
00:07:18,065 --> 00:07:19,065
At that time,

82
00:07:19,145 --> 00:07:21,865
the underground garage
was under construction.

83
00:07:21,945 --> 00:07:23,585
I took advantage of the moment

84
00:07:24,345 --> 00:07:27,065
and stuffed the arm bones into the cement

85
00:07:27,145 --> 00:07:28,785
and made a cement block.

86
00:07:29,305 --> 00:07:31,945
I thought this time, no one would find it.

87
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:34,305
But I didn't expect,

88
00:07:34,385 --> 00:07:36,585
after more than ten years,

89
00:07:36,665 --> 00:07:40,265
I'd be the one to dig it up myself.

90
00:07:45,345 --> 00:07:49,865
These bones have been
weighing on me ever since.

91
00:07:51,585 --> 00:07:53,025
I hate Yuanlongli!

92
00:07:53,745 --> 00:07:55,305
I hate it so much!

93
00:07:55,385 --> 00:07:57,705
I wish it were torn down sooner!
Just tear it down!

94
00:07:57,785 --> 00:08:01,345
And these bones
and all the monsters all gone!

95
00:08:01,985 --> 00:08:03,425
Gone for good!

96
00:08:03,945 --> 00:08:06,665
Then no one would care
about this case anymore!

97
00:08:07,185 --> 00:08:08,225
Never again.

98
00:08:25,545 --> 00:08:27,665
FAIR AND JUST, LOYAL AND TRUE

99
00:08:27,745 --> 00:08:29,505
What Qian Dajun said is mostly reliable.

100
00:08:30,025 --> 00:08:33,065
What he mentioned, the 1997 garage
and the rooftop incident,

101
00:08:33,144 --> 00:08:35,185
I did go through
those things with Uncle Ran.

102
00:08:35,264 --> 00:08:36,385
Preliminarily, it looks like Qian Dajun

103
00:08:36,465 --> 00:08:38,985
has nothing to do with Xu Meng
and her father's deaths.

104
00:08:40,664 --> 00:08:41,784
Qian Dajun's arrest

105
00:08:41,865 --> 00:08:44,785
means Yuanlongli
probably won't be demolished early.

106
00:08:45,305 --> 00:08:47,145
<i>We still have time to keep investigating.</i>

107
00:08:47,225 --> 00:08:51,425
Oh, and we should
circle back to Qian Dajun,

108
00:08:51,945 --> 00:08:54,425
question him again about
everything related to the June 30th case.

109
00:08:55,025 --> 00:08:57,545
<i>Maybe it'll lead to something bigger.</i>

110
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:58,465
Okay.

111
00:09:11,145 --> 00:09:11,985
Uncle He.

112
00:09:12,065 --> 00:09:13,905
Uncle He. Good afternoon.

113
00:09:14,905 --> 00:09:17,305
I was just appointed by the company

114
00:09:17,385 --> 00:09:22,225
as the Yuanlongli project's
head of redevelopment.

115
00:09:22,745 --> 00:09:24,065
JIN MANLANG, RELOCATION MANAGER

116
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:31,105
The company also promised
that if the demolition wraps up quickly,

117
00:09:31,945 --> 00:09:34,345
I'll be promoted to vice president.

118
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:37,145
-So…
-So, what's that got to do with me?

119
00:09:37,745 --> 00:09:39,225
Uncle He,

120
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:43,265
I'm not like Qian Dajun, I'm different.

121
00:09:43,785 --> 00:09:46,305
I believe in sincerity

122
00:09:47,145 --> 00:09:48,865
and peace above all.

123
00:09:53,545 --> 00:09:57,145
Uncle He, this place,
I'm not renting this place anymore.

124
00:09:57,225 --> 00:09:59,625
The rent will be returned double.

125
00:10:00,145 --> 00:10:01,465
Please move out.

126
00:10:02,105 --> 00:10:03,425
Double the rent.

127
00:10:07,705 --> 00:10:09,065
Wait.

128
00:10:19,825 --> 00:10:22,465
It's in black and white.
It's legal and valid.

129
00:10:22,545 --> 00:10:25,785
I paid, so I have the right to stay
for three full months.

130
00:10:25,865 --> 00:10:27,185
If you don't like it,

131
00:10:27,265 --> 00:10:29,185
you can go to court and sue me.

132
00:10:29,265 --> 00:10:31,225
How long it takes, I don't care.

133
00:10:32,265 --> 00:10:33,985
Uncle He, let's talk this over.

134
00:10:34,505 --> 00:10:36,105
I'll pay you triple rent.

135
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:40,105
Wang Laosan, come here.

136
00:10:41,265 --> 00:10:43,145
Get out of here.

137
00:10:45,945 --> 00:10:49,105
I've worked myself
to the bone all these years

138
00:10:49,185 --> 00:10:52,305
and finally got my chance
to turn things around.

139
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:55,105
Now, anyone who gets in my way,

140
00:10:55,185 --> 00:10:57,785
don't blame me, Jin Manlang,
for turning ruthless!

141
00:10:58,905 --> 00:11:02,025
Who was it that said "peace above all"?

142
00:11:02,825 --> 00:11:04,345
-Uncle He.
-See yourself out.

143
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:08,465
Well…

144
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:14,025
Wolf, don't get mad.

145
00:11:14,545 --> 00:11:15,745
Peace above all.

146
00:11:16,545 --> 00:11:17,745
Darn it!

147
00:11:20,985 --> 00:11:22,505
Wolf. Wolf!

148
00:11:25,105 --> 00:11:26,265
What's that?

149
00:11:26,345 --> 00:11:28,385
-That bag looks heavy.
-Did you see that?

150
00:11:30,505 --> 00:11:32,185
-That bag must be money.
-<i>Powering on.</i>

151
00:11:32,265 --> 00:11:35,025
<i>Good news! Good news!</i>

152
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:38,425
<i>The company has benefits for everyone!</i>

153
00:11:38,945 --> 00:11:40,345
<i>100k yuan per household,</i>

154
00:11:40,425 --> 00:11:41,905
<i>extra compensation.</i>

155
00:11:41,985 --> 00:11:43,305
<i>Just sign the contract.</i>

156
00:11:43,385 --> 00:11:44,625
-<i>Take the money now!</i>
-Let's go!

157
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:46,905
-Go take a look. Check it out.
-<i>Take the money now!</i>

158
00:11:46,985 --> 00:11:48,545
-<i>Limited spots.</i>
-Me first.

159
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:51,025
-<i>First come, first served!</i>
-Me first!

160
00:11:51,105 --> 00:11:52,305
Is it real?

161
00:11:52,385 --> 00:11:53,905
-They're really paying!
-Is it real?

162
00:11:53,985 --> 00:11:55,585
Come on! Line up!

163
00:11:55,665 --> 00:11:57,065
Line up, line up!

164
00:11:57,145 --> 00:11:58,505
<i>Benefits for everyone!</i>

165
00:12:02,225 --> 00:12:04,145
Don't rush!

166
00:12:04,665 --> 00:12:07,305
One at a time! Don't rush!

167
00:12:17,025 --> 00:12:18,705
One at a time!

168
00:12:25,865 --> 00:12:28,585
Meng, you've got to hold on,

169
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:30,385
stay and keep me company.

170
00:12:30,905 --> 00:12:33,185
Don't let a little money blind you.

171
00:12:48,065 --> 00:12:50,745
OFFICER HE, MENG'S BEEN DETAINED!

172
00:13:06,705 --> 00:13:10,185
Let Mr. Meng enjoy this

173
00:13:10,265 --> 00:13:13,145
Western symphony!

174
00:13:19,985 --> 00:13:21,225
So we're talking it out now?

175
00:13:22,305 --> 00:13:23,145
No more fighting?

176
00:13:27,665 --> 00:13:28,745
Why are you all staring at me?

177
00:13:29,585 --> 00:13:31,025
Keep the music going.

178
00:13:34,825 --> 00:13:36,185
Play something upbeat.

179
00:13:43,025 --> 00:13:45,185
Can't you see the door's open?

180
00:13:45,265 --> 00:13:46,225
Hurry up.

181
00:13:46,305 --> 00:13:49,385
Get Mr. Meng out here.

182
00:14:00,305 --> 00:14:02,945
STAGED SCENE. DO NOT IMITATE

183
00:14:04,585 --> 00:14:06,585
I'll send you all to hell!

184
00:14:06,665 --> 00:14:07,385
What are you doing?

185
00:14:07,465 --> 00:14:08,705
You old fool, want to die?

186
00:14:08,785 --> 00:14:10,025
You brat!

187
00:14:10,105 --> 00:14:11,625
I'll send you all to hell!

188
00:14:11,705 --> 00:14:14,065
That's illegal! You hear me?

189
00:14:14,145 --> 00:14:15,225
Call the police!

190
00:14:15,905 --> 00:14:17,585
Call the police now!

191
00:14:17,665 --> 00:14:19,145
I'll send you all to hell!

192
00:14:20,745 --> 00:14:21,865
<i>Come on!</i>

193
00:14:38,505 --> 00:14:41,145
Wolfie, you just won't go away.

194
00:14:50,225 --> 00:14:51,065
Uncle He.

195
00:14:51,745 --> 00:14:53,985
Qiao, what are you doing here?

196
00:14:55,305 --> 00:14:56,625
Come in, come in.

197
00:14:57,145 --> 00:14:59,305
Well, what do you want to drink?
I'll get it.

198
00:14:59,385 --> 00:15:00,625
Uncle He, don't bother.

199
00:15:01,705 --> 00:15:02,545
What's wrong?

200
00:15:04,105 --> 00:15:05,305
I…

201
00:15:05,385 --> 00:15:06,705
I didn't get our boss's approval,

202
00:15:07,785 --> 00:15:10,105
but I had finance sign off
on a 50k moving fee for you.

203
00:15:13,705 --> 00:15:14,945
Qiao, what's going on?

204
00:15:16,465 --> 00:15:19,705
Didn't we agree
to fulfill Ran's wish together?

205
00:15:19,785 --> 00:15:21,065
I know.

206
00:15:25,025 --> 00:15:27,705
I appreciate it, but I'm not moving.

207
00:15:28,305 --> 00:15:31,225
No matter the offer,
no matter the money, I won't move.

208
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:32,385
That's final! You should go.

209
00:15:32,985 --> 00:15:35,545
Uncle He. Uncle He.

210
00:15:36,665 --> 00:15:39,265
Our boss has reported you to the station.

211
00:15:42,225 --> 00:15:43,865
You should be ready.

212
00:15:47,185 --> 00:15:48,465
FORENSIC REPORT

213
00:15:53,945 --> 00:15:56,945
Xia, Xia…

214
00:15:57,025 --> 00:15:59,305
Xiaohe, go to Captain Zhao's office.

215
00:15:59,385 --> 00:16:00,345
What's going on?

216
00:16:01,305 --> 00:16:04,105
Captain Zhao, we're a private company.
It's not easy.

217
00:16:04,865 --> 00:16:08,065
This project can't be delayed anymore.

218
00:16:08,145 --> 00:16:09,865
If He Yuanhang keeps this up,

219
00:16:09,945 --> 00:16:12,265
it won't just hurt
our company's legal rights,

220
00:16:12,345 --> 00:16:15,865
it'll also undermine
what the residents deserve.

221
00:16:15,945 --> 00:16:20,185
Your criminal department
needs to stand up for people like us!

222
00:16:20,265 --> 00:16:21,225
I understand.

223
00:16:21,745 --> 00:16:23,945
We will figure this out quickly

224
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:25,305
and give you answers. Alright?

225
00:16:25,385 --> 00:16:26,785
Thank you, Captain Zhao.

226
00:16:26,865 --> 00:16:29,665
Please hurry. This can't wait.

227
00:16:29,745 --> 00:16:31,065
Come on. I'll walk you out.

228
00:16:31,145 --> 00:16:32,505
Okay, okay.

229
00:16:32,585 --> 00:16:33,705
-I'll head out then.
-Okay.

230
00:16:34,385 --> 00:16:36,305
Captain Zhao, stand up for us!

231
00:16:36,385 --> 00:16:38,585
-Alright.
-Okay. Take care.

232
00:16:42,425 --> 00:16:43,825
What's with He Yuanhang?

233
00:16:44,865 --> 00:16:46,065
Has he lost it again?

234
00:16:52,825 --> 00:16:55,705
Captain Zhao, Captain Qu,
since you're both here,

235
00:16:56,425 --> 00:16:57,345
I'd like to request

236
00:16:57,425 --> 00:16:59,745
reopening the investigation
into the June 30th case.

237
00:17:01,905 --> 00:17:03,465
June 30th?

238
00:17:03,545 --> 00:17:04,865
That's ancient history.

239
00:17:04,944 --> 00:17:07,665
He Xiaohe, you're just as crazy
as your dad.

240
00:17:07,745 --> 00:17:09,065
Isn't this mess enough?

241
00:17:10,905 --> 00:17:11,825
Captain Zhao,

242
00:17:13,305 --> 00:17:16,665
before Captain Ran passed,
he secretly reopened the June 30th case.

243
00:17:17,665 --> 00:17:21,224
These days, my dad and I
have been retracing his investigation.

244
00:17:21,305 --> 00:17:24,825
Now we have solid leads
proving Wu Shanlong was framed.

245
00:17:24,905 --> 00:17:26,105
The real killer is someone else.

246
00:17:29,505 --> 00:17:30,745
Any suspects?

247
00:17:32,545 --> 00:17:33,865
We are still checking.

248
00:17:36,585 --> 00:17:37,585
Not yet.

249
00:17:41,425 --> 00:17:42,305
Captain Zhao,

250
00:17:42,385 --> 00:17:44,865
this whole thing started because my dad

251
00:17:44,945 --> 00:17:47,985
found an unsent message
on Uncle Ran's old phone.

252
00:17:58,385 --> 00:18:00,065
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE
SAVED: 2003-01-31 13:09:37 TO: SIR

253
00:18:00,145 --> 00:18:01,705
RAN: SIR, THE JUNE 30TH CASE
WAS WRONG, ALL WRONG

254
00:18:01,785 --> 00:18:04,465
This message was written
on the day he died.

255
00:18:07,865 --> 00:18:11,185
Uncle Ran died with that regret.

256
00:18:21,385 --> 00:18:23,825
With the leads and evidence we have,
is it enough to reopen the case?

257
00:18:24,905 --> 00:18:25,825
I trust my dad.

